 Four patients including an 11-year-old boy receiving treatment for Coronavirus in Lagos have been discharged after recovering from the disease. Governor of the state, Babajide Sanwo-Olu, made the announcement in a Twitter post on Saturday. He said, “Today, four more patients; all male, including an 11-year-old boy have been discharged from the Lagos State isolation facilities to reunite with the society. “The patients; three from IDH, Yaba, and one from the Lagos University Teaching Hospital were discharged having recovered fully and tested negative twice to ‪#COVID19. “This brings to 50 the number of patients successfully managed and discharged from our isolation facilities.” 